Re: Number of connections?

Bitcointalk

2010-01-20 20:07:15 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Coins generate at the same speed with any number of connections >= 1.
   More connections just add redundancy.  If you only had one connection,
   what if that node is slow or busy, or only connected to you?  Having
   several connections increases the certainty that youʼre well connected
   to the network.  That hasnʼt been a problem in practice, the network is
   very thoroughly connected.  If you have 2 or 3 connections, youʼre
   fine.
